    "content": "\nWelcome to the Werewolf Game! In this game, players take on various roles, each with specific abilities.\nThe game alternates between day and night phases. During the night, special roles perform their actions.\nDuring the day, players discuss and vote to eliminate suspects. The goal is for the villagers to eliminate\nall the werewolves, while the werewolves aim to outnumber the villagers. Be careful who you trust!\n\n\n--- Role Introductions ---\nWerewolf Role Introduction:\nYou are a Werewolf. Your goal is to eliminate the villagers without being caught. Each night, you and your fellow\nwerewolves secretly choose one villager to eliminate. You must work together to deceive the other players during the\nday, while subtly protecting your fellow werewolves.\nTo better hide your identity, you may choose to pretend to be other roles to gain credibility. Since werewolves know each other's identities, pretending to be the Seer is a good way to gain villagers' trust.\nIf you manage to outnumber the villagers, you win the game.\n\n\nVillager Role Introduction:\nYou are a Villager. Your goal is to identify and eliminate the werewolves. During the day, you participate in discussions\nand voting to root out the werewolves. You have no special powers at night, but your ability to observe and reason\nis crucial to the village's survival. Work with other villagers and be careful whom you trust!\nAlthough you have no special skills, sometimes pretending to be another role can change the course of the game. For example, shielding a key player from harm could be your moment of glory.\n\n\nSeer Role Introduction:\nYou are the Seer. Each night, you can check the identity of one player to see whether they are a werewolf or not.\nYour knowledge is critical for the villagers' victory, so share it carefully. The werewolves will likely target you\nor pretend to be you to mislead others.\nAs the core of the good faction, the Seer is often the top target for werewolves to impersonate or kill. During the night, you should inspect players whose identities are uncertain (there is no need to check players who are highly suspected of being werewolves).\nWhen speaking during the day, your goal is to convince others that you are the real Seer. You must gather trust and\nshare your findings without exposing yourself too early. Even though revealing your identity might put you in danger,\na Seer trusted by both the Witch and the Guard can survive for at least three rounds if everyone acts accordingly.\nA good Seer will coordinate with the Witch and the Guard to divide responsibilities. For example, on the first night, the Guard protects the Seer, and the Witch doesn't use the antidote. On the second night, the Witch saves the Seer, and the Guard protects someone else.\n\n\nWitch Role Introduction:\nYou are the Witch. Each night, you will be told who has been attacked, and you must decide whether to use your antidote\nto save them or use your poison to eliminate another player. You only have one poison and one antidote, so use them wisely.\nDuring the daytime discussions, if the night ends without a death, you can reveal that you used your antidote to save someone, which may earn others' trust.\nTypically, you should use the antidote to save key players like the Seer, the Guard, or yourself, while the poison is best used to eliminate werewolves at night.\nHowever, be cautious: sometimes the werewolves will deliberately attack one of their own (self-knife strategy) to trick you into wasting the antidote, thereby boosting their credibility.\n\n\nGuard Role Introduction:\nYou are the Guard. Each night, you can choose one player to protect from being killed by the werewolves. You cannot protect\nthe same player two nights in a row. Your role is critical in keeping important players like the Seer or the Witch alive.\nYou are in a constant mental battle with the werewolves, trying to predict who they will target. It might not always be the Seer, as the werewolves might expect you to protect them and kill someone else. In general, you should avoid revealing your identity unless absolutely necessary.\n\n\n\n\nYou are Gail, your role in this game is wolf.\nWerewolf game starting. Initializing day-night cycle.\nSYSTEM: Starting day-night cycle for Day 1\nSYSTEM: Night 1 begins. Werewolves and special roles take actions.\nGuard has chosen to protect a player.\nRound Details:\n - Round Targets: {'Gail': 'Lamar', 'Lamar': 'Cedric', 'Virginia': 'Cedric'}\n - Remaining Werewolves: ['Gail', 'Lamar', 'Virginia']\n - Discussion Rounds Left: 5\n - Final Target: Cedric\n\nWerewolves have chosen their target.\nSeer has checked a player's identity.\nWitch has made her decision on potion use.\nSYSTEM: Day 1 begins. Players discuss and vote on potential suspects.\nNo candidates decided to run for sheriff. No sheriff in this game anymore.\nNo players deceased during the night.\nCedric's speech: Good morning, everyone. I hope you all had a peaceful night. I want to start by thanking the Guard for their protection last night. It's crucial that we all work together to keep each other safe. As for the rest of us, I haven't noticed any unusual behavior that would make me suspicious of any particular player. However, I do think it's important that we stay vigilant and pay close attention to any signs of deception or unusual actions. Let's all share our observations and thoughts so we can make an informed decision about who to banish. Remember, our goal is to eliminate the werewolves and protect our village. Let's work together to achieve that.\nGail's speech: Thank you, Cedric, for your insightful speech. I completely agree with the importance of working together and staying vigilant. It's crucial that we all do our part to protect our village and eliminate the werewolves. I want to offer my support in any way I can. If there are any specific tasks or observations that could help us make an informed decision, please let me know. I believe that by working together and staying focused, we can overcome this threat. Let's continue to support each other and make the best decisions for our village.\nGail's speech: Thank you, Cedric, for your insightful speech. I completely agree with the importance of working together and staying vigilant. It's crucial that we all do our part to protect our village and eliminate the werewolves. I want to offer my support in any way I can. If there are any specific tasks or observations that could help us make an informed decision, please let me know. I believe that by working together and staying focused, we can overcome this threat. Let's continue to support each other and make the best decisions for our village.\nIvan's speech: Thank you, Cedric and Gail, for your inspiring speeches. I completely agree with the importance of working together and staying vigilant. It's crucial that we all do our part to protect our village and eliminate the werewolves. I haven't noticed any unusual behavior that would make me suspicious of any particular player, but I have observed that some players seem to be more cautious or secretive than others. For example, Jean has been quite quiet and reserved, and Michael has been very talkative and eager to share his thoughts. I believe it's important that we all share our observations and thoughts so we can make an informed decision about who to banish. Let's continue to support each other and make the best decisions for our village. Remember, our goal is to eliminate the werewolves and protect our village, and we can only achieve this by staying focused and working together.\nJean's speech: Thank you, Cedric, Gail, and Ivan, for your speeches. I appreciate the emphasis on teamwork and staying vigilant. Ivan, I understand that you've noticed I've been quite quiet and reserved. I want to explain that I prefer to observe and gather information before speaking. I believe that this cautious approach helps me make more informed decisions about who to protect and who to trust.\n\nLast night, I protected Ivan, and I plan to protect Cedric tonight. I believe Cedric's leadership and dedication to the village's safety make him a valuable asset, and I want to ensure he remains safe. I am committed to working with all of you to eliminate the werewolves and protect our village. Let's continue to share our observations and work together to make informed decisions about who to banish.\nJerold's speech: Thank you, Cedric, Gail, Ivan, and Jean for your insightful speeches. I appreciate the emphasis on teamwork and staying vigilant. Last night, I checked Ivan, and I can confirm that he is not a werewolf. This information is crucial for us to make informed decisions about who to banish. I haven't noticed any unusual behavior that would make me suspicious of any particular player, but I believe it's important that we all share our observations and thoughts. Let's continue to support each other and make the best decisions for our village. Remember, our goal is to eliminate the werewolves and protect our village, and we can only achieve this by staying focused and working together.\nJohn's speech: Thank you, Jerold, for confirming Ivan's innocence. Your role in gathering information is crucial for us to make informed decisions. I want to express my gratitude for your efforts and support the village's safety. As we move forward, I believe it's important that we stay vigilant and work together to protect our village. However, I also think we need to gather more information before making a decision to banish someone. Let's be cautious and ensure we have solid evidence before taking any action. Remember, our goal is to eliminate the werewolves and protect our village, and we can only achieve this by staying focused and working together.\nLamar's speech: Thank you, Jerold, for confirming Ivan's innocence. Your role in gathering information is crucial for us to make informed decisions. I want to express my gratitude for your efforts and support the village's safety. As we move forward, I believe it's important that we stay vigilant and work together to protect our village. However, I also think we need to gather more information before making a decision to banish someone. Let's be cautious and ensure we have solid evidence before taking any action. Remember, our goal is to eliminate the werewolves and protect our village, and we can only achieve this by staying focused and working together. Let's continue to share our observations and work together to make informed decisions about who to banish.\nMichael's speech: Thank you, everyone, for your insightful speeches. I appreciate the emphasis on teamwork and caution. Ivan, I understand that you've noticed I've been quite talkative and eager to share my thoughts. I want to clarify that my verbosity is due to my eagerness to contribute to the village's safety and that I value everyone's input. Jean, I commend your cautious approach and your decision to protect Cedric. Your commitment to the village's safety is admirable. Let's continue to share our observations and work together to make informed decisions about who to banish. Remember, our goal is to eliminate the werewolves and protect our village, and we can only achieve this by staying focused and working together.\nVirginia's speech: Thank you, Jerold, for confirming Ivan's innocence. Your role in gathering information is crucial for us to make informed decisions. I want to express my gratitude for your efforts and support the village's safety. As we move forward, I believe it's important that we stay vigilant and work together to protect our village. However, I also think we need to gather more information before making a decision to banish someone. Let's be cautious and ensure we have solid evidence before taking any action. Remember, our goal is to eliminate the werewolves and protect our village, and we can only achieve this by staying focused and working together. I am committed to working with all of you to gather information and make the best decisions for our village. If any of you have any observations or information you'd like to share, please feel free to do so. Let's continue to support each other and make informed decisions about who to banish.\nAll players have completed their speeches for today.\nMichael has been banished from the game.\nBanishment votes:\nIvan voted for abstain\nGail voted for Jean\nCedric voted for Michael\nJean voted for abstain\nMichael voted for abstain\nLamar voted for Cedric\nJohn voted for Michael\nVirginia voted for Gail\nJerold voted for Michael\n(Note: The voting order reflects only the system's query sequence and does not imply any strategic alignment or motive.)\nPlayer Michael has been eliminated from the game.\nSYSTEM: Starting day-night cycle for Day 2\nSYSTEM: Night 2 begins. Werewolves and special roles take actions.\nGuard has chosen to protect a player.\nRound Details:\n - Round Targets: {'Gail': 'John', 'Lamar': 'John', 'Virginia': 'Ivan'}\n - Remaining Werewolves: ['Gail', 'Lamar', 'Virginia']\n - Discussion Rounds Left: 4\n - Final Target: John\n\nWerewolves have chosen their target.\nSeer has checked a player's identity.\nWitch has made her decision on potion use.\nSYSTEM: Day 2 begins. Players discuss and vote on potential suspects.\nPlayers deceased during the night: John, Jean\nPlayer John has been eliminated from the game.\nPlayer Jean has been eliminated from the game.\nCedric's speech: Thank you all for your insightful speeches. I appreciate the emphasis on teamwork and caution. Lamar, I noticed you have some suspicion towards me, and I want to assure you that I have no ill intentions. My goal is to help protect our village and eliminate the werewolves. The deaths of John and Jean last night are concerning, and we need to be vigilant and gather more evidence before making any decisions. Let's stay cautious and ensure we have solid evidence before taking any action. I encourage everyone to share their observations and work together to make informed decisions about who to banish. Remember, our goal is to eliminate the werewolves and protect our village, and we can only achieve this by staying focused and working together.\nGail's speech: Thank you, Cedric, for your insightful speech. I completely agree with the importance of working together and staying vigilant. It's crucial that we all do our part to protect our village and eliminate the werewolves. The deaths of John and Jean last night are concerning, and we need to be cautious and gather more evidence before making any decisions. Let's stay focused on our goal and work together to protect our village. I encourage everyone to share their observations and work together to make informed decisions about who to banish. Remember, our goal is to eliminate the werewolves and protect our village, and we can only achieve this by staying focused and working together.\nGail's speech: Thank you, Cedric, for your insightful speech. I completely agree with the importance of working together and staying vigilant. It's crucial that we all do our part to protect our village and eliminate the werewolves. The deaths of John and Jean last night are concerning, and we need to be cautious and gather more evidence before making any decisions. Let's stay focused on our goal and work together to protect our village. I encourage everyone to share their observations and work together to make informed decisions about who to banish. Remember, our goal is to eliminate the werewolves and protect our village, and we can only achieve this by staying focused and working together.\nIvan's speech: Thank you, Cedric and Gail, for your insightful speeches. I completely agree with the importance of working together and staying vigilant. Cedric, I appreciate your response to Lamar's suspicion. Your dedication to the village's safety is clear, and I believe you have no ill intentions. Let's stay focused on gathering more information before making any decisions. Lamar, I understand your concerns, but I think it's important that we don't jump to conclusions without solid evidence. Virginia and Jerold, I look forward to hearing your perspectives as well. Let's continue to support each other and make informed decisions about who to banish. Remember, our goal is to eliminate the werewolves and protect our village, and we can only achieve this by staying focused and working together.\nJerold's speech: Thank you, Cedric, Gail, and Ivan for your insightful speeches. I appreciate the emphasis on teamwork and caution. Ivan, I want to confirm that I checked you last night, and I can assure everyone that you are not a werewolf. This information is crucial for us to make informed decisions about who to banish. Cedric, I also want to reaffirm that I have no reason to suspect you of being a werewolf. Your dedication to the village's safety is clear, and I believe you have no ill intentions. Let's stay focused on gathering more information before making any decisions. Lamar, I understand your concerns, but I think it's important that we don't jump to conclusions without solid evidence. Virginia and Jerold, I look forward to hearing your perspectives as well. Let's continue to support each other and make informed decisions about who to banish. Remember, our goal is to eliminate the werewolves and protect our village, and we can only achieve this by staying focused and working together.\nLamar's speech: Thank you, Cedric, Gail, Ivan, and Jerold, for your insightful speeches. I appreciate the emphasis on teamwork and caution. Cedric and Gail, your dedication to the village's safety is clear, and I believe you have no ill intentions. Ivan and Jerold, I completely agree with the importance of gathering more information and staying cautious. The deaths of John and Jean last night are concerning, and we need to be vigilant and gather more evidence before making any decisions. Let's stay focused on our goal and work together to protect our village. I encourage everyone to share their observations and work together to make informed decisions about who to banish. Remember, our goal is to eliminate the werewolves and protect our village, and we can only achieve this by staying focused and working together.\nVirginia's speech: Thank you, Cedric, Gail, Ivan, and Jerold, for your insightful speeches. I appreciate the emphasis on teamwork and caution. Cedric, I want to reaffirm that I have no reason to suspect you of being a werewolf. Your dedication to the village's safety is clear, and I believe you have no ill intentions. Gail, your support and leadership are crucial for us to stay focused on our goal. Ivan and Jerold, your contributions and observations are invaluable. The deaths of John and Jean last night are concerning, and we need to be vigilant and gather more evidence before making any decisions. Let's stay focused on our goal and work together to protect our village. I encourage everyone to share their observations and work together to make informed decisions about who to banish. Remember, our goal is to eliminate the werewolves and protect our village, and we can only achieve this by staying focused and working together.\nAll players have completed their speeches for today.\nLamar has been banished from the game.\nBanishment votes:\nIvan voted for Lamar\nGail voted for abstain\nCedric voted for Lamar\nLamar voted for Ivan\nVirginia voted for Cedric\nJerold voted for Lamar\n(Note: The voting order reflects only the system's query sequence and does not imply any strategic alignment or motive.)\nPlayer Lamar has been eliminated from the game.\nSYSTEM: Starting day-night cycle for Day 3\nSYSTEM: Night 3 begins. Werewolves and special roles take actions.\nGuard has chosen to protect a player.\nRound Details:\n - Round Targets: {'Gail': 'Virginia', 'Virginia': 'Virginia'}\n - Remaining Werewolves: ['Gail']\n - Discussion Rounds Left: 1\n - Final Target: Virginia\n\nWerewolves have chosen their target.\nSeer has checked a player's identity.\nWitch has made her decision on potion use.\nSYSTEM: Day 3 begins. Players discuss and vote on potential suspects.\nPlayers deceased during the night: Virginia\nPlayer Virginia has been eliminated from the game.\nCedric's speech: Thank you, Jerold, for confirming Ivan's innocence. Your role in gathering information is crucial for us to make informed decisions. I want to express my gratitude for your efforts and support the village's safety. Ivan, your cautious approach and dedication to the village's safety are clear, and I believe you have no ill intentions. Gail, your support and leadership are also crucial for us to stay focused on our goal. Cedric, I want to address the suspicion that was raised towards you earlier. I have no reason to suspect you of being a werewolf, and I believe your dedication to the village's safety is clear. Let's stay focused on gathering more information before making any decisions. Lamar, I understand your concerns, but I think it's important that we don't jump to conclusions without solid evidence. Let's continue to support each other and make informed decisions about who to banish. Remember, our goal is to eliminate the werewolves and protect our village, and we can only achieve this by staying focused and working together.\nGail's speech: Thank you, Cedric, for your insightful speech. I completely agree with the importance of working together and staying vigilant. Your dedication to the village's safety is clear, and I believe you have no ill intentions. I want to echo your call for caution and emphasize the importance of gathering more information before making any decisions. Let's stay focused on our goal and work together to protect our village. I encourage everyone to share their observations and work together to make informed decisions about who to banish. Remember, our goal is to eliminate the werewolves and protect our village, and we can only achieve this by staying focused and working together.\nGail's speech: Thank you, Cedric, for your insightful speech. I completely agree with the importance of working together and staying vigilant. Your dedication to the village's safety is clear, and I believe you have no ill intentions. I want to echo your call for caution and emphasize the importance of gathering more information before making any decisions. Let's stay focused on our goal and work together to protect our village. I encourage everyone to share their observations and work together to make informed decisions about who to banish. Remember, our goal is to eliminate the werewolves and protect our village, and we can only achieve this by staying focused and working together.\nIvan's speech: Thank you, Cedric and Gail, for your insightful speeches. I completely agree with the importance of working together and staying vigilant. Your dedication to the village's safety is clear, and I believe you have no ill intentions. Jerold, thank you for confirming Ivan's innocence. This information is crucial for us to make informed decisions. I want to echo your call for caution and emphasize the importance of gathering more information before making any decisions. Let's stay focused on our goal and work together to protect our village. I encourage everyone to share their observations and work together to make informed decisions about who to banish. Remember, our goal is to eliminate the werewolves and protect our village, and we can only achieve this by staying focused and working together.\nJerold's speech: Thank you, Cedric, Gail, and Ivan for your insightful speeches. I appreciate the emphasis on teamwork and caution. I want to reaffirm my commitment to the village's safety and share the information I have gathered. Last night, I checked Cedric, and I can confirm that he is not a werewolf. This information is crucial for us to make informed decisions. I also want to confirm Ivan's innocence, as I checked him on the first night and found that he is not a werewolf. Cedric and Ivan, your dedication to the village's safety is clear, and I believe you have no ill intentions. Let's stay focused on gathering more information before making any decisions. Gail, your support and leadership are also crucial for us to stay focused on our goal. Let's continue to support each other and make informed decisions about who to banish. Remember, our goal is to eliminate the werewolves and protect our village, and we can only achieve this by staying focused and working together.\nAll players have completed their speeches for today.\nNo player was banished due to a tie.\nBanishment votes:\nIvan voted for Gail\nGail voted for Cedric\nCedric voted for Cedric\nJerold voted for Gail\n(Note: The voting order reflects only the system's query sequence and does not imply any strategic alignment or motive.)\nSYSTEM: Starting day-night cycle for Day 4\nSYSTEM: Night 4 begins. Werewolves and special roles take actions.\nGuard has chosen to protect a player.\nRound Details:\n - Round Targets: {'Gail': 'Jerold'}\n - Remaining Werewolves: ['Gail']\n - Discussion Rounds Left: 1\n - Final Target: Jerold\n\nWerewolves have chosen their target.\nSeer has checked a player's identity.\nWitch has made her decision on potion use.\nSYSTEM: Day 4 begins. Players discuss and vote on potential suspects.\nPlayers deceased during the night: Jerold\nPlayer Jerold has been eliminated from the game.\nCedric's speech: Thank you, Jerold, for confirming Ivan's and my innocence. Your role in gathering information is crucial for us to make informed decisions. Ivan, your cautious approach and dedication to the village's safety are clear, and I believe you have no ill intentions. I want to address the suspicion that was raised towards me earlier. I have no reason to suspect any of you of being a werewolf, and I believe my dedication to the village's safety is clear. Let's stay focused on gathering more information before making any decisions. Gail, your support and leadership are also crucial for us to stay focused on our goal. Let's continue to support each other and make informed decisions about who to banish. Remember, our goal is to eliminate the werewolves and protect our village, and we can only achieve this by staying focused and working together.\n\nHere's the current game state:\n\n{\n  \"days\": 4,\n  \"day/night\": \"day\",\n  \"alive_players\": [\n    \"Ivan\",\n    \"Gail\",\n    \"Cedric\"\n  ],\n  \"sheriff\": null\n}\n\nNow, it is your turn to speak.\nYou are the 2 player to speak this round.\nHere is what the players before you have said:\nCedric: Thank you, Jerold, for confirming Ivan's and my innocence. Your role in gathering information is crucial for us to make informed decisions. Ivan, your cautious approach and dedication to the village's safety are clear, and I believe you have no ill intentions. I want to address the suspicion that was raised towards me earlier. I have no reason to suspect any of you of being a werewolf, and I believe my dedication to the village's safety is clear. Let's stay focused on gathering more information before making any decisions. Gail, your support and leadership are also crucial for us to stay focused on our goal. Let's continue to support each other and make informed decisions about who to banish. Remember, our goal is to eliminate the werewolves and protect our village, and we can only achieve this by staying focused and working together.\n\nAt this stage, each player is expected to share their opinions and reveal any information they have gathered, helping the group make an informed decision about who to banish next. Follow these steps to organize your thoughts and decide your action:\n\n0. Based on your current role and objectives, what do you need to achieve in order to win? Do you need to gain more trust, deflect suspicion, or accomplish something else? Break down your ultimate goal into smaller, actionable steps you need to complete during this round of speech. Record your plan in role_objectives.\n\n1. Think about your speaking position. You are the 2 player to speak. What have the previous players said? Is there anything that directly impacts your position (e.g., claims against you, information about your role)? Should you respond to their claims? If so, how should you respond? Store your analysis in response_plan.\n\n2. Evaluate the statements made by the players who spoke before you. Whose words seem credible? Who seems suspicious, possibly a werewolf? Should you ally with someone or criticize another player’s statements? Analyze each player’s speech in speech_analysis.\n\n3. What is your main goal for this round? Do you want to provide information, reveal your role, or shift the game's momentum to gain trust? Should you claim a specific role, mislead other players, or offer false information? Based on this, decide what you will say. Record this in goal_strategy.\n\n4. How do you think your speech will be perceived? Will it make you appear more trustworthy, or will it raise suspicion? Consider how others will react to what you say. Record your perception_analysis.\n\n5. **Additional Considerations Based on Your Role**:\n   - If you are the **seer** (or claiming to be one):\n     - Should you reveal who you checked last night and the results of your checks from the previous night? Why or why not? Should you direct the guard or witch on who to protect tonight?\n   - If you are the **guard** (or claiming to be one):\n     - Should you reveal whom you protected last night and who you plan to protect tonight? Will you speak the truth or lie about your protection? Should you coordinate with the witch and the seer?\n   - If you are the **witch**(or claiming to be one, not recommended, since rel witch have a poison which can kill you at night):\n     - Should you reveal your identity? If so, should you reveal who you saved last night (if it was a peaceful night)? Should you discuss the plan for future nights? Will you tell the truth or lie about your actions?\n   - If you are the **sheriff**:\n     - Should you reveal your \"badge flow\" (i.e., who you would pass the sheriff badge to if you were to die)? If you are also the seer, should you reveal who you plan to check tonight? Should you declare what you will do with the badge based on your findings (e.g., pass it to a trusted player, or destroy it if you find a werewolf)?\n   - **If you are a werewolf** :\n     - Should you claim to be a different role? If so, what role should you claim? Has anyone else already claimed this role? How would this affect your credibility? Will this claim deflect suspicion from you or raise doubts? How will other players react to this claim, and will it help you survive longer? What risks are involved if someone else counterclaims or reveals your lie?\n\n6. Based on the above, create a detailed outline of your speech in speech_outline.\n\n7. What is your final decision? Write your complete speech content in action, including your final thoughts on how it should impact the game.\n\n\n=============================[Optional Daily Tasks]=============================\nHere are the tasks relevant to you:\nprotect_seer: Keep the seer alive by focusing on their safety.\nexile_werewolf: Coordinate with others to vote out a suspected werewolf.\nYou may incorporate them if appropriate."
